This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it proposes an unsupervised visual tracking method using a Siamese correlation filter network. It also mentions the use of multiple-frame validation and cost-sensitive loss to facilitate unsupervised learning, which are common techniques in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves training a CNN model on large-scale unlabeled videos, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. 

The use of unsupervised learning methods and the focus on leveraging unlabeled or weakly labeled data may also place this paper in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. 

The paper's focus on visual tracking and the use of raw videos may also suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) category. 

Finally, the paper's use of a Siamese correlation filter network for tracking may also place it in the robotics (cs.RO) category, as this technique has been used in robotics applications such as object tracking for autonomous vehicles.
